Joel R. MeyerPartner










                        Los Angeles
                    
 
                2029 Century Park EastSuite 300Los Angeles, CA 90067
		    
P:310-284-3772
F:310-284-3894









Joel R. Meyer is a partner in the Los Angeles office of Barnes & Thornburg LLP. Mr. Meyer is a member of the firm’s Litigation Department, focusing on complex business litigation. Mr. Meyer has litigated a variety of complex civil disputes, including those involving breach of contract, business torts, trade secrets, product liability, toxic torts, consumer class actions, construction, and healthcare law. 
Mr. Meyer’s recent engagements and accomplishments include the following: 

Obtained summary judgment on behalf of defendant in a putative class action in which the plaintiff alleged multiple violations of the Telephone Consumer Protections Act 
Obtained summary judgment on behalf of a chemical supplier in a multi-million dollar CERCLA cost recovery action 
Served as a trial counsel and obtained complete defense verdict for an international asset management business after a four-week trial in which the plaintiff, a former hedge fund manager, sought more than $100 million in damages based on contract, fraud, and defamation claims 
Served as a trial counsel and obtained complete defense verdict on behalf of a publicly traded, for-profit educational company on claims it breached a commercial lease 
Obtained summary judgment on behalf of an international clothing retailer in an Americans with Disabilities Act compliance dispute 
Represented medical groups, a healthcare management company, and their owners in multiple lawsuits including defending against claims for breach of contract, fraud, defamation, tortious interference, breach of fiduciary duty, and unfair competition 
Defended a litigation services company against claims that it conspired to misappropriate a competitor’s trade secrets when it recruited and hired a competitor’s salesperson 
Defended dietary supplement manufacturer in alleged national consumer class action for claims of false and misleading advertising 
Representing an independent film production company in various contract disputes 
Representing hotel owner in action against contractors and product suppliers relating to renovation of hotel showers 
Defending a global ink manufacturer in toxic tort/product liability actions located in jurisdictions throughout the United States 
Mr. Meyer earned his B.A. in economics from the University of California, Los Angeles, and his M.A. in political science from California State University, Fullerton. Mr. Meyer attended law school at Indiana University School of Law in Bloomington, where he earned his J.D., magna cum laude. While in law school, Mr. Meyer served as managing editor of the Indiana Law Journal and was selected for membership in the Order of the Coif.
Prior to joining Barnes & Thornburg, Mr. Meyer was an associate in the Los Angeles office of Akin Gump Strauss Hauer & Feld LLP. He is a member of the California Bar and admitted to practice before the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit, and before the U.S. District Courts for the Central, Eastern, Northern, and Southern Districts of California.















