In Memoriam: Joel Meyer of Meyer Sales | enLIGHTenment - The Lighting Industry Trade Publication























































































 






















  





 









In Memoriam: Joel Meyer of Meyer Sales

May 5, 2016Staff EditorNews, People 



Lighting industry veteran Joel Meyer of Meyer Sales in Florida passed away unexpectedly. He was an independent sales representative for Artcraft, among other lines. Our condolences to the Meyer family. 
“Joel was our representative, colleague, and friend for over 30 years. In addition to his sales function, he stocked our products locally and served on the Artcraft Sales Council and Product Council. We could always count on Joel for his honesty, integrity, and plain old common sense,” says Howard Bernstein of Artcraft. “Joel was very well respected and liked and will be sorely missed. This is a very big loss for all of us,” he adds. 
Noting that Meyer spent his entire career in the lighting business, showroom owner Ric Jolie of Benson’s Lighting & Fans in Miami calls Joel, “one of the good guys” in lighting, adding, “His work ethic, integrity, humor and friendship will be sadly missed.”
A service in celebration of Joel’s life will be held Friday at 10:00 AM at Star of David synagogue in Tamarac.


